"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Long-acting preparations are administered by deep INTRAMUSCULAR administration only and NEVER given intravenously. Subcutaneous administration is not recommended due to variable absorption and increased risk of local site reaction. Details shown are specific to the preparations and forms available in US, unless otherwise noted. Dosing, administration and other details listed in licensed product information may differ for other forms and by country. Consult official product information for detail.",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"     LAI: intramuscular long-acting injectable (also known as \"depot\" injection).",
"     <br/>",
"     * Not available in US.  Product details shown from Canada product monograph available at: file://webprod3.hc-sc.gc.ca/dpd-bdpp/index-eng.jsp  accessed on March 6, 2012.",
"     <br/>",
"     <span class=\"bullet\">",
"      &bull;",
"     </span>",
"     Significant dosage reduction required for older or debilitated adults, patients with low cardiac output or hepatic or renal insufficiency. Certain products are not recommended in renal insufficiency. For additional information, see Lexi-Comp drug reference included with UpToDate.",
